   On-Line Professional Licensing



   __________ search
           (*)   My CA


   Welcome to Security Guards On-Line Licensing System

   The On-line Professional Licensing System is available for Security
   Guard Registrations only to
   submit initial applications, renew licenses, request duplicate
   licenses, and make address changes.
   Initial applicants must have their fingerprints processed through
   Live-Scan to apply on-line

   You are eligible to renew online if:
     * Your license expires within the next 3 months.
     * Your license is delinquent by no more than 60 days.
     * You have no outstanding fines with Bureau of Security and
       Investigative Services.

              The following credit cards are accepted:
               VISA, MASTERCARD, DISCOVER
        There is a $2.00 convenience fee added to all on-line transactions
   that require a payment.

   FIRST TIME USERS -  You will need your:
     * Social Security Number
     * Credit Card Information
     * Registration number if you are renewing   -   Example
       (alpha/numeric = G1234567)
     * eMail Address   -   Please enter correct email address   Example (
       jsmith@aaa.com )
     * Click here to get started, or click on Professional Licensing link
       in left column.

   RETURNING USERS -  You will need your:
     * User ID
     * Password
     * Credit Card Information
     * Click here to get started, or click on Professional Licensing link
       in left column.

   For assistance in the on-line process you may contact the Department of
   Consumer Affairs eGovernment Team at (916) 322-7834 between the hours
   of 8-5 PST Monday through Friday, or email to egov@dca.ca.gov.
   For licensing information you may contact the Bureau of Security and
   Investigative Services at (916) 322-4000.
   If you are a AOL user please read the AOL User Browser Requirements
   here or on left menu bar.


